JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC)'s 54th elective conference is set to kick off on Saturday at Nasrec, Johannesburg.  The start of the conference was delayed when National Executive Committee (NEC) members met on Saturday morning to discuss three court rulings on Friday that impact on the conference and branch delegates who are allowed to vote.  WATCH: Party officials barred by courts will not vote at conference The NEC decided that ANC officials barred by courts from attending its leadership conference this weekend would not take part in voting. ANC elective conference 2017 programme by eNCA.com on Scribd eNCA